description:
Candi Liyangan adalah situs purbakala berupa candi dan kawasan permukiman di lereng timur Gunung Sundoro, tepatnya di permukiman warga Dusun Liyangan, Desa Purbasari, Kecamatan Ngadirejo, berjarak sekitar 20 kilometer arah barat laut dari kota Temanggung, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah. Situs ini baru ditemukan pada tahun 2008.[1]

Penemuan pertama berupa talud, yoni, arca, dan batu-batu candi. Penemuan selanjutnya sebuah bangunan candi yang tinggal bagian kaki dan di atasnya terdapat sebuah yoni yang unik, tidak seperti umumnya, karena yoni ini memiliki tiga lubang. Penelitian dan penggalian lebih lanjut dilakukan Balai Arkeologi Yogyakarta pada 2010 dan 2011 menyimpulkan bahwa situs tersebut bukan merupakan candi besar tetapi sebuah perdusunan Mataram Kuno. Berdasar gambaran hasil survei penjajakan Balai Arkeologi Yogyakarta menyimpulkan bahwa Situs Liyangan merupakan situs dengan karakter kompleks; indikasi sebagai situs permukiman, situs ritual, sekaligus situs pertanian. description:
Playing outdoors promotes well-being and physical development.

Kids are naturally drawn to playing outside and there are numerous benefits of outdoor play: 
- it allows them to explore their environment
- develop muscle strength and coordination
- gain self-confidence. 

Playing actively outdoors also increases:
- flexibility
- fine and gross motor skills
- is related to the development of a wide variety of physical skills, including those involved in sports.

Time for outdoor play is diminishing, contributing to more sedentary lifestyles, disconnected from the natural world. 

Recognizing the importance of outdoor play is essential for young children's healthy growth.

This video highlight the role families in creating quality outdoor play opportunities.

Q: What is pretend play and why is it important in imaginative play in child development?

A: Fantasy and dramatic play grow children's brains. ‚Ä¶pretend play is a healthy part of every child's social, emotional, and cognitive development and should not be feared by parents or educators. Pretend play allows children to learn about their dislikes and likes, and aids them in experimenting in role play and to think about what they‚Äôve observed. This is a child's way to go on to work out new life issues, for example what they find scary and confusing. Children develop important complex social and higher order thinking skills, it requires further thinking and planning as well as balancing their own ideas with others also cultivating social and emotional intelligence. 


Q: What age does pretend play start?

A: The act of pretending is believed to be inbuilt because it occurs universally and begins promptly between the ages of 18-24 months.
*As advised by Wikipedia, link below: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make_believe#Critical_period


Q: What are pretend play examples and ideas?

A: Playing with an object as if that object is alive; some examples of pretend play include being superheroes, playing ‚Äòmummies and daddies‚Äô, playing shopping, dress‚Äêups, playing flying to the moon, tea‚Äêparties, playing trucks in the sandpit and playing with dolls and teddies to name a few.

description:
Kasai Rinkai Park (ËëõË•øËá®Êµ∑ÂÖ¨Âúí Kasai Rinkai K≈çen) is a park in Edogawa, Tokyo, Japan, which officially opened on June 1, 1989.[2] The park includes a bird sanctuary and the Tokyo Sea Life Park aquarium. It was built on reclaimed land which includes two manmade islands, a observation deck and a hotel. It is the second-largest park in the 23 wards of Tokyo (after Mizumoto Park).[3]

The 117-metre (384 ft) tall Diamond and Flower Ferris Wheel opened at the park in 2001.[3] On a clear day, it affords views of Tokyo Bay, Chiba, Edogawa, Tokyo Disneyland, and Mount Fuji. It is reportedly the second tallest ferris wheel in Japan.[4]

About a third of the park is designated a sea bird sanctuary, which houses a Sea Bird Centre that provides information on the local bird species.[4] The park also has two beaches on artificial islands. The west island is connected to land by the Kasai Nagisa bridge and is a popular place for recreation.[2] The east island is closed to the public as a protected bird habitat and Ramsar site since 2018.[1]

The park is always crowded during the 'hanami' period of spring, when the Japanese party under cherry trees in bloom.

description: With the dissolution of her marriage and the death of her mother, Cheryl Strayed has lost all hope. After years of reckless, destructive behavior, she makes a rash decision. With absolutely no experience, driven only by sheer determination, Cheryl hikes more than a thousand miles of the Pacific Crest Trail, alone. WILD powerfully captures the terrors and pleasures of one young woman forging ahead against all odds on a journey that maddens, strengthens, and ultimately heals her.

title: 2020 Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony
tags: montgomery county,maryland,sports,hall of fame,induction,ceremony,Tom Brown,Johnny Holliday,Jeri Ingram,Roy Lester,Curtis Pride,Amy Wood
description:
Hello and welcome to the Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame 2nd Annual Induction Ceremony

Curtis Pride (Baseball), Johnny Holliday (Broadcasting), Amy Wood (Field Hockey), Jeri Ingram (Tennis), Tom Brown (Baseball and Football) and the late Roy Lester (HS Football Coach) are all stellar in their history of representing our community and in their commitments to make Montgomery County a better place.

Curtis Pride's story--born severely hearing impaired, yet excelled in three sports--will bring tears to your eyes. Tom Brown played in the pros in two sports; baseball for the Senators and won three NFL title rings with the Green Bay Packers. Jeri Ingram still holds records in Montgomery County and the University of Maryland. Coaches, like Amy Wood and Roy Lester, are often the unsung heroes behind the stars. But they not only build athletes, they build young men and women who are our county's future. And Johnny Holliday! He is much, much more than the voice of the Terps. Humble and generous of spirit.

Olympic Gold Medalist and 2019 Inductee Dominique Dawes delivers a special message after landing a surprise opening.

Thank you for joining us!

Please visit our website to learn more about this year's inductees, past inductees, and how you can help support the Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame https://mcshf.org

title: Due Date
description: Robert Downey Jr. plays Peter Highman, an expectant first-time father whose wife's due date is only days away. As he hurries to catch a flight home to Los Angeles from Atlanta to be at her side for the birth, his best intentions go completely awry when a chance encounter with aspiring actor and disaster-magnet Ethan Tremblay (Zach Galifianakis) leads to the two of them being tossed off the plane and placed on a no-fly list...while Peter's luggage, wallet and ID take off without him. With no alternatives in sight, Peter is forced to hitch a ride with Ethan and his canine traveling companion on what turns out to be a cross-country road trip that will destroy several cars, numerous friendships and Peter's last nerve. title: Outdoor Adventures
description: When Caillou, Grandpa and Daddy go on a canoe trip, Caillou is amazed to see a dragonfly, a blue heron, and a beaver working on his beaver lodge. While Caillou and his family are on a picnic at the park, his beach ball accidentally rolls into a pond. Caillou sees a family of ducks swimming in the pond and wants to take a closer look. Dad shows Caillou a neat trick to call the ducks. When a white rabbit eats a bunch of carrots set aside for a picnic lunch, Caillou and Rosie go looking for him. They soon discover that it isn't a wild rabbit, his name is Snowball and he belongs to Mr. Hinkle's sister. On another day, Caillou and his family are leaving for a picnic in the country but the ride feels very long for Caillou. When they stop at a gas station, Caillou spots some cows in a field next to a picnic area. The family decides to have the picnic there, where they have a close encounter with some cows. Caillou learns about patience when he goes fishing with Daddy and Grandpa at the pier. But learning about patience is hard, can Caillou wait long enough to catch his own fish?

description:
Going outside to play is not always possible. Often it may be due to the weather, but there are many other reasons why outdoor play may not be an option! It's in times like these that it's essential to organise fun indoor games for the kids to fight boredom. Watch this video for a list of indoor games for kids, which will keep them thoroughly engaged.

Indoor group games for kids are fun too and help them learn to become part of a team. There's no limit to the number of games you can play indoors, but it's important to organise different games from time to time, as children get bored easily. Try the different games listed in this video and watch as your kids have a gala time at home!

description:
Documentary about Club Penguin, for it's 15th anniversary.

Featuring:
Chris Hendricks
Lance Priebe
Lane Merrifield

Club Penguin was an online-based, massively multiplayer online role-playing game (abbreviated as a MMORPG) created by Disney Canada Inc. (previously New Horizons Interactive) in the summer of 2005. The game was founded by Lance Priebe, and co-founded by Lane Merrifield, and Dave Krysko. There were over 330,000,000 penguin accounts created and played in over 190 countries. It was estimated that over 150 million people worldwide play Club Penguin. It was discontinued on March 30, 2017.

title: Keep kids engaged with easy outdoor activities you can do at home
tags: gardening,activities for kids,environment,lisa taylor,seed planting,outdoors,outside,backyard
description:
Garden Educator-in-Residence Lisa Taylor shares her activities for making garden activities for kids fun and educational at the same time.  Lisa teaches an "original garden-based literacy curriculum" at schools in Seattle and Shoreline, and is an author of the Maritime Northwest Garden Guide, 2nd ed. and Your Farm in the City: An Urban Dweller‚Äôs Guide to Growing Food and Raising Animals.

Seed Planting
-Planting seeds is a classic. Now is the time to grow seeds under lights or sow them directly in the garden.  
-For best results, pre-moisten the soil so it readily absorbs water, plant seeds in the soil at a depth 2 to 3 times the thickness of the seed, and give them a gentle pat so that seed touches soil on all it's surfaces.      
-If you want to give your seeds a leg up, start growing them inside without lights. Place them in a sunny window and move outside as soon as seeds sprout
-No garden, no problem. Sprout seeds that are in your cupboard. Mung beans, raw sunflower seeds, grains, and other beans. Use about 1 teaspoon of dried seeds in a glass jar. Keep them moist and rinse them daily ‚Äì many will sprout in 4 or 5 days.
-Plant a container of microgreens. Repurpose a plastic container then fill with a little soil and plant some lettuce seeds, you can grow tiny salad greens in 2 to 3 weeks.

Critter Hunting
-Kids like bugs and frankly bugs are more dynamic then plants!
-Keep a Critter Journal or photo diary. Then go hunting!
-Creatures of the Earth. Look for critters that live under rocks, old pots, mulch, or brick. Identify any that you see using books or technology. Draw pictures and learn about habits and habitats. Then create some habitat by building a bug house with a pile of rocks and plants.
-Creatures of the Air. This takes more patience but carefully observing flying creatures is super fun and often surprising. Practice being a flower by sitting still while you watch the bees at work. Identify any flying insects and catalog them in your Critter journal.
-If you get excited you could start a worm bin or build a mason bee house . . . creatures are a gateway to the garden for young people.

Digging In
-Designate a place for digging and building ‚Äì get some sturdy small shovels, assorted pieces of wood, bricks, and such. Let them go! Use big muscles, test out engineering ideas then add water and see what happens. Digging big holes and trenches are the stuff of childhood memories ‚Äì just call 811 before they dig!

title: How to Design Interactive Outdoor Play, that Survive Harsh Environments?
tags: designing interactive outdoor play,interactive outdoor play,outdoor play,iot playground,interactive playground,designing for outdoor play,public play,blockly,drakryggen,ecorado,link√∂pings kommun,uppsala universitet,toy design,designing fun,designing play,playfulness,serious play,design thinking,playgrounds,computer games,children's play,mixed reality,internet of things,playful internet of things,serious about play and games,outdoor playground for kids
description:
A new playful IoT (internet of Things) playground have recently opened in Link√∂ping's kommun. We talk about the design work, and focus on robust technology in IoT and interactive public and outdoor play design.

The playground is designed to be interactive, as well as malleable and adaptable. This way the interactions and play design can change, even after the physical artifacts are in the ground. To do this the design project, Play IT, has focused on play design and interaction design, taking different forms of play into account. We have built hybrid games or hybrid play, in the borderland between computer games and outdoor play, while still avoiding screen interfaces and thereby creating a "heads up" form of gaming, or HUG as it is sometimes reffered to.

The Play IT project is a collaboration between the companies Drakryggen and Ecorado, Link√∂ping municipally, Uppsala university, and the Royal Institute of Technology (KTH). It is part of IoT Sweden, and funded by Vinnova, Energimyndigheten and Formas.

-----

Here in the Creative Geek we help semi-professional to professional designers, creators, tinkerers and makers to understand and make games, toys and playful technology. We focus on play, playfulness and interaction, rather than on the games in themselves.

This can include not only computer games and board games, but also such different activities as role playing games, larp, playful IoT, augmented and virtual reality, escape rooms, pervasive games, playground design and even gamification and play based learning.

We are here for you who do not only consume, but also create playful geek culture, in one form or another. If you are a self-defining geek, passionate about creating, this is the place for you!

The channel is hosted by Dr Jon Back, a researcher and play designer with background in interaction design, and a long running focus on creating experiences through games and play.

In this channel, we believe that play is something that‚Äôs worth taking seriously. And we believe you think so to!

We try to post weekly, so click on the subscribe button, and tap that little bell, and together we will learn more about making play happen!

SKELETON PLAY DOUGH: Here‚Äôs a fun way to get into the Halloween spirit, üéÉ play dough style! This invitation to build a skeleton was super fun. ü¶¥ And the set up is so simple ‚Äî black play dough (recipe below!), cotton swabs, googley eyes, and cookie cutters! üëç üôå Read on belowüëá for how to make black play dough at home, and swipe üëâ to see more of this invitation to build a skeleton. ‚ò†Ô∏è
- 
NO COOK PLAY DOUGH RECIPE 
Mix Together 
‚Ä¢ 1 1/4 cup of all-purpose flour 
‚Ä¢ 1/3 cup of fine salt 
‚Ä¢ 2 tablespoon of cream of tartar 
‚Ä¢ 2 tablespoon coconut oil (optional) Add 
‚Ä¢ 3/4 cup of boiling water (I mix in food coloring to water prior to heating water up in microwave). 
‚Ä¢ I wear gloves and mix the *very hot* play dough by hand to make sure that the dough is kneaded thoroughly, which spreads the heat, dissolving the granules to make a smooth texture. 
Note 
*If too sticky add a little more flour 
*If too dry add a little more water 
*Coconut Oil gives the play dough a super silky texture. You could also use glycerine. Alternatively, other vegetable oil will work too, but I‚Äôve found that coconut oil makes it super silky! 
*Cream of Tartar is a preservative, it makes the play dough have a longer shelf life. 
-
üèó DIRT AND ROCK SLIME // Slime ‚Äî love it üòç or hate it üòñ? My kiddos love it, so I‚Äôve grown to embrace it, üëç so much so that when they asked me if we could combine their love of dirt and rocks with slime, I jumped to the challenge! ü§óüòÇ Swipe üëâ to see more of this gooey slimy construction play, and read on below üëá for the recipe. Plus, pop on over to my stories for some slime cleaning tips! üëå

HOW TO: Combine 1 cup water with 1 cup clear glue. Mix in 1 cup dirt OR rocks (we made batches of each). Add 1 cup liquid starch. If slime is too sticky add little more liquid starch. 
- 
‚ö†Ô∏è CAUTION: Slime should be prepared by adult. Always wash hands after playing and making slime. ‚ö†Ô∏è

üñê MUDDY PRINTS üñê // Do you have a play that totally takes over your little ones? For my boys, it‚Äôs any kind of water play, üí¶ especially one that combines water with their next favorite thing, dirt - aka, making mud.ü§ó

‚ú® GOLD SPARKLE SLIME 
WHAT YOU‚ÄôLL NEED 
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup water 
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup clear glue (or a 5 oz bottle) 
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp biodegradable glitter 
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp gold acrylic paint 
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp baking soda 
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsps contact solution (make sure it is a true 2 tbsps because contact solution often foams when pouring out) 
- 
HOW TO 
(1) In a bowl, mix water and glue (2) Mix in glitter (3) Mix in acrylic paint (4) Mix in baking soda (5) Mix in contact solution and it should begin to form into slime-like consistency (6) Cover your hands with contact solution and knead the slime. It will be sticky at first, but keep on kneading! If it is still too sticky you can always add more contact solution. - Parental supervision required. Always be sure to wash hands after playing with slime!

title: Outdoor Play Areas for KIDS
tags: Outdoor Playsets for Kids,outdoor play structures for kids,outdoor paysets,outdoor play structures,kids outdoor play structures,outdoor playsets,outdoor play sets2020,play sets w/slides,trampolines in backyards,backyard inground trampolines,backyard kids campsites,play sets with inground slides
description:
Outdoor Playsets for Kids

Today‚Äôs video is all about Outdoor playsets for Kids and hang out areas for kids in landscape design. Play structures with/without slides, kid‚Äôs hangouts, playhouses, boulder trails, trampolines, backyard campsites . . . outdoor kids areas - as part of the landscape design.

We start out in the Thomas‚Äô ninja-equipment-play-room with turf flooring. What a great outdoor room to grow up with? The heavy-duty hooks in the ceiling hold numerous ‚Äòkids play‚Äô workout equipment and fun-toys strong enough for adults too. Add a turf floor versus concrete so any mishaps or crashes have softer landings. This is the best! The 3 boys in the home love it! Imagine the hours of playtime they will spend here, and they do use it. If they are not having fun in the playroom they scurry down the hillside to the trampoline at the bottom of the yard and spend hours there. Years down the line if not used by the kids as much when they grow into teens, this room can be turned  into a outdoor living space.

This video will share all kinds of kids retreats ‚Äì away from parents and yet in your backyard. Places to play away from the adults ‚Äì to come up with fun games and to invent the hide & seek type of activity we all enjoyed at one time ourselves.Playhouses can finish off a landscape design. Trampolines help us get our jump on. Kids need a place hang out on their own!

Gibson‚Äôs‚Äô Backyard

In this private retreat, choose the relaxing comfort of an outdoor living area with a perfect view of all activities. A lower deck provides a kids‚Äô social area. However, kids and teens do like to gather around the firepit. Near all the action, this firepit has custom wood seat walls for many guests to enjoy the firelight. It is especially nice to have the sunken spa so close it. Adults like to soak for a while, however, kids might have the tendency to hop in and out, hanging at the fire or goofing off in the in-ground hot tub. They can also run & jump around the playset. Lot‚Äôs of fun for all.

Dickson‚Äôs Family Focused Backyard

This Backyard Pergola family-focused landscape design draws you in to relax while children have ample areas to play and explore. Access from two patio doors makes toddler playtime easy for mom to orchestrate while taking care of daily inside activities ‚Äì the custom fence with latch gates keeping both youth and dogs from straying too far. Later Mom can join in the fun ‚Äì perhaps to walk the meandering pathway with unique boardwalk and rope bridge accent or to enjoy the child‚Äôs play area.

Some additional landscape design elements include: brick matching hardscape trim on circular patio and steps, brick planters lined with specimen plants, boulder accents, tiered raised garden beds and large open grass areas for child‚Äôs play.

Myer‚Äôs Backyard

For kids and young adults, a sunken trampoline gets ‚Äúoohs and ahhs‚Äù as young and old give it a try. Oh, the thrill of a trampoline! It‚Äôs ageless! Close to the trampoline, a two-level child‚Äôs play structure top off the many attractions found in this family-friendly outdoor haven.

Waxman Property

This roomy outdoor living area hots spots in front of the fire and a dining table to enjoy eating alfresco with a large group of guests. An added white iron bistro set adds an extra bit of charm. You may enjoy the aroma of fresh baked pizza while watching all areas of the landscape. Note the spacious grass area with child‚Äôs play structure allows entertainment for the young in clear view of the relaxing adults!

Dawson Backyard Campsite

Across the lush green lawn and down into the woods ‚Äì an awesome camp ground sits in a clearing offering unlimited hours of family togetherness. It is hard to match this ultimate in outdoor living . . .

Edelberg Living Space

It all starts with a desire to transform one‚Äôs everyday living space.  Extending that space out your door and into nature, you can double your living space.  By adding features that appeal to all ages you add practical living space that doubles your enjoyment. Kids like to play outside and yet, they love to hang with mom and dad. When you provide space that allows both it brings the family closer.

Outdoor playsets for Kids video shares great photos of play structures, slides, playhouses, tire swings, and kids play in this outdoor living video. Thank you for joining Paradise Restored for outdoor play sets 2020. We love creating outdoor spaces with kids in mind and we would love to help you. Complimentary Consultation? You got it!

We are happy to answer questions - help design/build your landscape renovations. Have you seen our latest landscapes in our Portfolio? It‚Äôs pretty interesting to see the before and after photos. See backyards reversed and transformed.

Thanks for watching - thanks for subscribing . . .

description:
Kids stuck at home on the Covid-19 shutdown? Check out 11 healthy games and activities for kids to do at home - indoor and outdoor ideas included! How to keep your kids healthy and active at home during the Corona Virus school hiatus.

3:55 HEALTHY INDOOR ACTIVITIES

TWISTER GAME LINK: https://amzn.to/3bjzvyP

JUST DANCE VIDEO GAME LINK: https://amzn.to/33t0t48

Most experts agree that children ages 6-17 need at least one hour of moderate-to-vigorous intensity exercise everyday. Children and youth who meet this recommendation have been linked to higher levels of fitness, lower body fat, stronger bones and muscles, improved cognition, and reduced symptoms of depression. (https://www.cdc.gov/healthyschools/physicalactivity/guidelines.htm)

Typically this requirement is met at school (P.E. and recess), with extra curricular activities, or organized sports after school.

But what about the summer months when the kids are home more often? Or extended breaks from school? Or worse - what if there‚Äôs a viral pandemic crippling the country and schools are all on shutdown and all sporting and other recreational events are indefinitely suspended? (I‚Äôm looking at you, Corona Virus of 2020)

Well - that‚Äôs where this video comes in. As a doctor of physical therapy I understand how important activity is in children. As a father of four (who now has to try to figure out how to homeschool 4 children) I know it‚Äôs important for all our sanity that the kids get out an move a little bit!

So that‚Äôs why in this video I want to share with you 11 great ideas that you and your children can do to stay healthy, strong, and active at home.

This list is by no means meant to be all-inclusive; these are simply some ideas that work well in my family.

If you have anything you would like to add or other ideas that have worked well for your family - please leave them in a comment down below so we can build this list, create a fun community of ideas, and ultimately help each other out!

title: Adaptive Outdoor Recreation: Tree Climbing for Kids with Disabilities
tags: c.s. mott children's hospital,physical medicine and rehabilitation,recreational therapy,therapeutic recreation,adaptive outdoor recreation,kids with disabilities,tree climbing,activities for children with disabilities,disability visibility,accessibility,accessible,disability rights,ableism,activities for kids with special needs,happy kids,children's health,pediatric health,inclusive design,inclusive,disabilities,#adaptive,Recreation Therapy,outdoor recreation
description:
Adaptive outdoor recreation modifies standard outdoor activities, like tree climbing, to make them accessible for those with physical handicaps.  It is a type of recreational therapy which focuses on the importance of leisure time as a part of the total rehabilitation process.  At Michigan Medicine, adaptive outdoor recreation is one of many interventions used by recreational therapists to improve the physical, cognitive, emotional, social and leisure needs of clients.  

Funded by Michigan Medicine Physical Medicine & Rehabilitation (PM&R) and a generous grant from Dance Marathon at the University of Michigan (DMUM), the tree climbing event is open to families in the community with children aged 5 and older that have a disability.  Tree climbing, in particular, is unique in that it‚Äôs an activity open to the whole family, encouraging fun, exercise, socialization and spending time outdoors.  Ultimately, providing healthier minds and bodies while empowering participants to enjoy life.

For more information on Michigan Medicine‚Äôs Therapeutic Recreation Program, please visit: https://medicine.umich.edu/dept/pmr/clinical-services/therapeutic-recreation 

For more information on University of Michigan Adaptive and Inclusive Sports Experience (UMAISE), please visit: https://medicine.umich.edu/dept/pmr/patient-care/core-practice-areas/university-michigan-adaptive-inclusive-sports-experience-umaise

We provide all in one waterproofs, all in one snowsuits, waterproof jackets, waterproof trousers and waterproof dungarees for children from age 9 months to 11 years. We also sell childrens swimwear including baby and childrens wetsuits, reusable swim nappies, pool shoes and beach boots.

The game of dodge ball is thought to have originated in Africa over 200 years ago. Once used to train men in strength and agility, it is now an organised sport played by teams of all ages.  There are various rules and versions of this game, some using multiple balls in play at one time, some teams playing to a professional level.

To play dodge ball with children, you do need a few rules.  Make sure your ball is fairly soft and light to avoid injury.  Encourage children to aim for the ankles and feet only.  Avoid any physical contact with other players.

This is a very simplified version of the game and loads of fun.  Mark out your area of play.  Position a thrower at either side of the pitch (or all four sides).  The thrower aims the ball at the players ankles, once hit, the player is out and leaves the game or can join the throwers at the side.  

Our team just loved playing dodge ball and would have happily played all day!  Playing with the little ones needed a bit of adult involvement.  It really is game for all ages.  Anyone can play.  No excuses.  Get your trainers on and join in the fun!

tags: traditional outdoor play,rounders,outdoor play,kids waterproof clothing,schools waterproofs
description:
Kids waterproofs from Rain-shine

http://www.rain-shine.co.uk

SIGN UP TO OUR ENEWSLETTER FOR YOUR FREE CHAPTER FROM OUR EBOOK ON MUDDY PLAY - VISIT WWW.RAIN-SHINE.CO.UK
Let your children have fun outside whatever the weather. Rain-shine are the supplier of quality children's waterproof clothing throughout the UK.

We provide all in one waterproofs, all in one snowsuits, waterproof jackets, waterproof trousers and waterproof dungarees for children from age 9 months to 11 years. We also sell childrens swimwear including baby and childrens wetsuits, reusable swim nappies, pool shoes and beach boots.

At Rain-shine we love to play outdoors.  We believe that being outdoors should be fun and we also believe that having fun doesn't need to cost money or need anything more than some friends and some imagination.  This summer we are trying out some traditional childhood games.

Rounders is a British game which dates back to the 1700s!  It's played in two teams, the 'fielders' and the 'batters'.  The batters take turns to hit the ball then run round a wide circle of 'bases'.  The fielders have to catch the ball and reach the base first to knock the batter out of the game.  When all the batters have had a turn, the teams swap over.  Each team collects points for each full circuit of the bases.  

Rounders is still played in many Scottish schools.  It's a great way to get kids working together in teams, helps improve hand-eye coordination, and needs concentration and speed to win the game.  Although rounders is normally played in larger teams, our little team of five had great fun with our simplified version our rounders bat is now a firm favourite with the boys!  Why not put on your running shoes and give it a go?

Let your children have fun outside whatever the weather.  Rain-shine are the supplier of quality children's waterproof clothing throughout the UK.
We provide all in one waterproofs, all in one snowsuits, waterproof jackets, waterproof trousers and waterproof dungarees for children from age 9 months to 11 years. We also sell childrens swimwear including baby and childrens wetsuits, reusable swim nappies, pool shoes and beach boots.
Port and Starboard, Pirates, Shipwreck, Ship Captain or Hit the deck.  Like most traditional games, this one has been passed through the generations with widely varying names and rules.  Whatever you choose to call it, it's loads of fun.  You can follow our rules and actions, or make up your own.  

One person is the captain.  They stand to the side and shout instructions to their pirate crew.  The Pirates then have to act out the commands as quickly as possible.  To add to the challenge, you can play an elimination game where the last person to preform each action sits out.  The last remaining pirate becomes the new captain and play begins again.  

We used these simple commands:

Port (left)
Starboard (right)
Bow (back)
Stern (front)
Climb the riggings
Scrub the decks
Shark attack
Captains coming

Who is the best pirate in your crew today?

title: Preservation
description: PRESERVATION is a relentless psychological thriller set in the decaying sprawl of rural America. A camping trip for newlyweds Mike and Wit takes an unexpected turn when they are joined by Mike's brother, Sean, a former marine. When their tent is stolen overnight and they are left without food or water, the brothers turn on each other. A random act of violence becomes a game of cat and mouse. A weekend in the woods becomes survival of the fittest. A young couple must survive their failing marriage. An Iraq veteran must survive his violent past. And Wit must outsmart the predators hunting their prey. Christopher Denham's second feature film is an unexpected and unflinching exploration of violence in the digital age.

description:
Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber  http://bit.ly/1Nu8V9c

Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber
The Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber is a great toy for children between the ages of 2 to 6. This climber has a wavy slide, high walls on each side, a tunnel underneath the wide platform and large steps for easy climbing. The angle of the slide is not too steep but is quite exciting for toddlers. 
Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber Features and Specifications 
Wavy slide. The angle of the slide and its wavy shape make it great fun. 
Underneath tunnel. The underside of the platform acts like a tunnel or a fort for lots of fun filled hours.
Safe. The tall walls on the side make it safe for the kids who might eagerly jump on the slide.
Wide platform. The platform is big enough to fit 2 kids on it.
Strong built. Kids run, jump and play a lot, so this climber was designed to withstand the most active kids.
Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber Pros and Cons 
Pros 
Fun wavy slide
Wide platform 
Tall walls on the side
Space to crawl underneath
Strong for very active kids
Cons 
The back of the slide has no safety bar or rail.
Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber Reviews 
One of our recent customers who purchased the Little Tikes Hide & Slide Climber said: ‚ÄúMy 2 year old, got it as a present for his birthday. After 15 minutes of assembly it was ready and his play buddies went to play, giving us adults a bit of a break. I am quite satisfied with the purchase and it also made my son happy ‚Äú. 
Another satisfied parent said: ‚ÄúI got it for my grandkids and, after I put it together in the hallway, I realized I wanted it in the living room. The problem is that it didn‚Äôt fit through my door so I had to take it apart and put it back together. The built quality is great and my grandkids love it‚Äú.
One of the recent customers also said: ‚ÄúIt is great value for a backyard climber. I wish it had something at the back of the slide. I am worried that my daughter might fall, though that hasn‚Äôt happened yet‚Äù.

Product Description
Up, down, over, under, through, around - the Little Tikes Hide & Seek Climber is perfect for kids who have mastered mobility and are just learning how to use it. Children are constantly active, and this play set gives them a productive place to learn where all that effort goes. It helps them learn, on a very fundamental level, linguistic concepts like prepositions and scientific ideas like velocity. More importantly, it's fun. Children love racing around it, chasing each other or just showing off for Mom. The low height is perfect for their developing balance and gives them a sense of security that will grow into confidence. With an easy rock wall, gentle slide, and connector bridge for climbing over or crawling under, there's a ton of activities to keep your little one occupied for hours. Additional Features: Slide length: 28.25 in. Ground to platform: 18H in. Climbing wall: 12.50H in. Total weight: 24 pounds About Little Tikes Founded in 1970, the Little Tikes Company is a multi-national manufacturer and marketer of high-quality, innovative children's products. They manufacture a wide variety of product categories for young children, including infant toys, popular sports, play trucks, ride-on toys, sandboxes, activity gyms and climbers, slides, pre-school development, role-play toys, creative arts, and juvenile furniture. Their products are known for providing durable, imaginative, and active fun. In November of 2006, Little Tikes became a part of MGA Entertainment. MGA Entertainment is a leader in the revolution of family entertainment. Little Tikes services the United States from its headquarters and manufacturing facility in Hudson, Ohio, but also operates several manufacturing and distribution centers in Europe and Asia. Great play set for kids' physical development. Includes easy-climbing rock wall and gentle-slope slide. Connector bridge for perching on top and crawling under. For children 1 to 4 years old. For indoor or outdoor use.
From the Manufacturer
This kids climber play set promises a terrific time with loads of adventure and fun both indoors and out. Lightweight and sturdy, the castle play set is easy to assemble.

title: ‡§¶‡§æ‡§¶‡•Ä Terrace Gardening with kids | Pluck Brinjals outdoor activities | Nature play and plant care
tags: terrace garden,rooftop garden,roof garden,plant care,house plant care,terrace gardening,eggplant,kids growing plants,outdoor activities,outdoor activities for toddlers,outdoor activities for preschoolers,activities for kids,nature walk,nature play,pluck brinjals,plants for kids,playing on terrace,kids garden,gardening with kids,kids friendly,family friendly,fun activities for kids at home,kids activities at home
description:
Kids are enjoying and learning amidst nature on their terrace garden. They are plucking brinjals with their grandmother. Notice how carefully they handle the plants. They are enjoying the flowers only by smelling them and not plucking them.
Watch the video to learn what Shagun teaches Shloka about why we should not pluck the flowers. Notice the kids identifying the plants while having fun. Don't you like to know it, Then watch the video completely. brinjal is the king of vegetables.

title: Virtual Behind the Scenes at Romano Gymnasium
description:
Join former UMD Bulldog Basketball Head Coaches and current athletic administrators, Karen Stromme and Gary Holquist in a Virtual Bulldogs Behind the Scenes tour of Romano Gymnasium exploring recent renovations including historical perspectives.

Romano Gymnasium has been the home of Bulldog Men‚Äôs and Women‚Äôs Basketball and Volleyball for over a half-century. The historic facility opened December 12, 1953 and underwent a renovation in 1986 as well as a significant remodel throughout 2019-2020. Romano Gymnasium is the largest indoor gathering space on the UMD campus and one of the larger venues in Northern Minnesota. The space is a highly visible area of campus that is seen by all students, University employees, and community. It is often looked at as the ‚Äúfront porch‚Äù of the institution. Romano Gymnasium is much more than an athletic team space, event space, and teaching space - it is a community space.

*This event was recorded via Zoom on October, 20 2020.*

Bulldogs Behind the Scenes is a UMD alumni event that gives you an inside look at local industry leaders. Alumni and friends will enjoy facility tours, access to company leadership, and connecting with each other through curiosity and learning.

Learn more about our virtual programs at d.umn.edu/alumni

You can learn more about Romano by visiting https://umdbulldogs.com/sports/2013/8/30/RomanoGym.aspx

title: Exuberant Animal Solo Short Form
tags: health,fitness,physical education,athletic training,play
description:
This is a functional movement sequence designed to pump your body into a state of exuberance. It will also enhance your athletic performance and help to prehabilitate you against injury. The moves are conceptually simple, but contain thousands of variations that will keep you engaged over time. You can perform this set as a warm-up or as a stand-alone practice, any time you feel the need. Perform outdoors and barefoot when possible, or wherever the need for movement arises. In any case, follow these core principles:

Use your whole body to perform each movement.
Bend your knees and get your hips "talking to your shoulders."
Breathe powerfully.
Use your hips, core and torso to power the moves.
Experiment with a variety of stances and challenge yourself with combinations of big and small, fast and slow.
This sequence is an integral part of the Exuberant Animal Trainer curriculum: all Exuberant Animal Trainers are expected to master the basic sequence. Find our more about becoming an Exuberant Animal Trainer.

title: Open Tables
description: Set within the walls of the trendiest Chicago restaurants and behind the closed doors of exclusive dinner parties, Open Tables explores colliding stories of love lost, love found and all the details between. The ensemble characters - friends and acquaintances navigating through blind dates, missed connections and odd encounters come together over dinner with a number of ulterior motives. Sam and Kate host the party in hopes that sparks will fly between Kate‚Äôs younger, idealistic sister Cassie and their shy friend Ryan. Joining them at the table is Jon and Dana, a couple whose seemingly perfect relationship is anything but. As the group sits down to shared plates and good wine, stories - and possibly lies - emerge. Ryan boasts about his sexual escapades in France to impress Cassie, Jon and Dana share the story of their meeting while dating other people and the betrayal that led to their becoming a couple, and Sam and Kate tell the group about their friend Hannah who falls in love with Dean, a man who has no memory. Told in flashbacks but always returning to the warm glow of the dinner table, the first act of Open Tables presents a world where true love prevails, the guy gets the girl (or the guy gets the girl and the guy) and where even the most complicated of people can find their soul mate, even when - and sometimes because - their circumstances are unique. After the meal ends and the parties go their separate ways, the second act of Open Tables lets the sometimes heartbreaking aspect of love surface and the reality that not everyone lives happily ever after is considered. Jon and Dana deal with the realities of betraying someone you love, while Dean gets his memory back and dumps Hannah, and Cassie unimpressed by Ryan‚Äôs boastfulness, ignores him until the thought of being alone compels her to go on an unusual first date.

title: Jesse Colin Young - Out Of The Darkness
description: Jesse Colin Young's career is best defined by his recording of " Get Together" with the Folk Rock band the Youngbloods. This one song pivoted him to the stadium and outdoor concert scene in 1969 while he toured  with greats like Led Zepplin, Crosby, Stills, Nash and Young, The Allman Brothers , Janis Joplin, The Doors and many more. His career spans 50 years. This  2015 concert is Jesse's way of giving back to  USA Veterans  and supporting an new project called Saratoga WarHorse that has successfully served vetrans from all wars who suffer from debilitating PTSD. Jesse is joined by Juilliard 's  master musician's, Charles Yang and Peter Dugan. The film covers all of Jesse's songs that were performed  live that night and  additional interviews from folks who participated in the making of this historic event. In that one concert night $250,000 was raised for the Saratoga WarHorse program  for our veterans.

title: Oh Dad, Poor Dad, Mama's Hung You  in the Closet and I'm Feeling So Sad
description: Wealthy Madame Rosepettle (Rosalind Russell) and 25-year-old Jonathan (Robert Morse) arrive at the Port Royal Hotel on a tiny Caribbean island with the man of the family in tow, literally; he's been dead for many years and his stuffed corpse travels with them in a coffin. Madame is the kind of woman who keeps piranhas and Venus Flytrap plants as pets, and controls her son's life down to deciding what meal he'll have for breakfast, lunch, and dinner (a hamburger and a maraschino cherry). Jonathan is kept indoors at all times and isn't allowed to mix with the outside world, though the hotel "babysitter," Rosalie (Barbara Harris), slips in through the window and flirts with the easily rattled young man. Madame is being courted by drunken millionaire Commodore Roseabove (Hugh Griffith), and while she welcomes his advances, her attention is diverted by trying to make sure that her son stays "pure." Rosalie isn't one to be put off by the meddling matriarch, so she doubles her efforts to get at Jonathan, who wants Rosalie too but might be pushed over the edge by the attention.

title: Outdoor leadership kids show
tags: Outdoors,Outdoor Channel (TV Network),Outdoor Education (Literature Subject)
description:
Derek and I created this video for the final project in our outdoor leadership class taught by Karen Warren at Hampshire College. 

Our aim was to create a children‚Äôs TV show that would help kids get outside and see the importance of the outdoors in a funny light hearted way. 

The process of creation for this video was very light hearted, spontaneous and improvisational. We were able to draw on each other‚Äôs strengths and play with ideas. Because of our approach in playfully creating this video the project did not seem like work, it was a very fun activity that we both were exited to work on. 

I think this is a good example of the power of play to create. We both had a blast and used playful mindsets to accomplish a final project that was more then just another paper but instead a fun experience as well as a final product that many people can enjoy!

title: BLEU! - Interactive dance and theatre for children
tags: bleu!,compagnia tpo,tpo company,cie tpo,interactive theatre,teatro ragazzi,jeune public,marseille capital culture,davide venturini,francesco gandi,luca tomao,cristina d'alberto,elsa mersi,interactive theater,theatre for children,theater for children
description:
compagnia TPO in co-production with

Teatro Metastasio Stabile della Toscana 
Th√©√¢tre Joliette Minoterie 
Marseille-Provence 2013, Capitale europ√©enne de la culture
 
artistic direction Francesco Gandi, Davide Venturini
choreography Anna Balducci
dance for two performers
visual environment Elsa Mersi
sound environment Spartaco Cortesi
computer programming and interactive systems Rossano Monti
costumes Fiamma Ciotti Farulli
props Livia Cortesi
organization Valentina Martini, Francesca Nunziati, Chiara Saponari

Borrowing from classical mythology and from stories that compose the very Mediterranean area itself, Bleu! narrates the meeting of two characters: a Sailor and a magical and mysterious being who is a Sea Nymph. It all starts when "She" drops a pearl into the sea so that "He" can find it. The sailor will have to undertake an adventurous journey, plowing the sea waters and diving to the lowest abysses, transforming the story into an active discovery and search for knowledge.
Stars are the guiding presence in Bleu! and they serve to transversely unite one stage scene to another, giving viewers firm reference points in the story. Indeed by following the paths of the stars, we will face stormy waters and howling winds; we will meet some sea dwellers; we will dance, play music, and create moments of play for a small, close-knit crew.
In Bleu! the natural elements of the marine environment become the setting of a virtual journey undertaken by actors and audience alike. The centrally situated stage is floored with a large dance carpet; on this surface are projected images evoking a beach where small treasures have washed ashore and are ready for the taking. Above the stage hangs a large and mobile spiral structure made of tulle fabric; in constant and slow transformation, its surfaces become the screen for projections which allow images to float in mid-air, making the space an even more totally immersive experience.

In this setting small groups of children will interact with the two dancers and the "found" objects, as well as with the play's images and sounds, in a process of unveiling the secret life of the marine environment.

title: New 'playscape' coming to Forest Park
tags: Forest Park Forever,Albrecht Nature Playscape,Anne O‚ÄôC. Albrecht,forest park playground,st louis park
description:
Next spring, children and families will have a new place to play in Forest Park when a new 17-acre playscape is complete.

The Anne O‚ÄôC. Albrecht Nature Playscape is in its final stage of construction and is scheduled to open in late spring 2021, according to a press release from Forest Park Forever. 

Located near the World‚Äôs Fair Pavilion, the playscape is an "experiential green space," that encourages visitors to connect and engage with nature and features nine activity areas called Mounds, Spring, Meadow, and Wetland.

Forest Park Forever will work with the City of St. Louis to ensure there will be proper health and safety protocols and guidelines when the playspace opens, the release said. 

Between now and the anticipated late spring opening, Forest Park Forever said it will give some glimpses of the project on social media and offer tours, either virtually or in small groups. 

Construction on the project began in spring 2019 and it is funded by donations made to Forest Park Forever.

The film begins story of between two families, Christians and Hindus: Stephen (Nagesh) and Seetaramaiah (Satyanarayana) have been best friends since college and so have their respective sons, Moses (Anand Raj) and Balaramaiah (Devan). Moses' younger brother, Robert (Maharshi Raghava) and Balaramaiah's younger sister, Janaki (Rajitha) fall in love with each other. Against their families' wishes, they elope. Ever since then, the tie war is going between two families.

After 25 years later, Chandu (Jagapati Babu) comes to the village and announces that he is the son of Robert and Janaki along with his friend Gopi (Sudhakar). He wants to reconcile the feuding families. Chandu stays in the house of the loud & frightful Nadabrahmam (AVS). He gradually endears himself to both families. Later, both his grandmothers suggest marriage. To avoid the situation, Gopi suggests that Chandu tell them that he is married. Chandu decides that this is the only way, thus lying that he is married to a Hindu-Christian like himself, Nirmala Mary.

Suddenly, Nirmala Mary (Ravali) arrives. Chandu is confused, as she was just a figment of his imagination. After several encounters, Nirmala Mary comes clean with Chandu, telling him that she is the only child of Robert and Janaki. She then confronts Chandu, asking him why he wants to unite the two families. Then Chandu reveals his past.

Chandu while living in the city, he lived next to a ladies' hostel, where Nandini (Raasi) daughter of Balaramaiah, was his resident. As she and her friends were trying to find a good song for a competition, Chandu indirectly helps her and falls in love with her. However she treats him as only a good friend. When Chandu was about to confess his love for her, Nandini instead tells him about her love for Lawrence, Moses' son. Hearing their plan to marry without their parents' consent due to the Robert-Janaki problem, Chandu volunteers to unite the families so that they can marry with the blessings of their families.

After listening to this Nirmala respects Chandu's character of making his lovers marriage with her lover and she also volunteers him and they carry out the mission. Meanwhile Balaramaiah learns of Nandini-Lawrence love. The news spreads quickly like wildfire and both families now think they have run away and want to kill the members of the other family. Meanwhile, Chandu has reconciled the grandparents of the two families. Only the fathers and the lovers are his main concern. At the end, he manages to unite the lovers and their families in a logical manner.

After the marriage, the truth of Chandu's appearance is revealed, by arrival of Robert & Janaki. Later, the families ask him to marry Nirmala (whose actual name is Priyadarshini) to make him a member of their family. However, he refuses, telling them that he loved a girl and does not want to think of anyone else.

description:
Join us this weekend as we begin a new, two-week sermon series, ‚ÄúAll About Grace.‚Äù Today, we hear about what grace can lead to. We‚Äôll hear about how we‚Äôre all trying to measure up to something, but only grace works.

Talk About It!
- "There are two ways through life‚Äîthe way of nature and the way of grace." Do you agree with that statement? If so, describe what each of those lives looks like.
- In what ways can you say "no" to ungodliness this week? How can grace help you with that?
- If godliness is disadvantaging yourself for others, in what ways can you be godly this week?

‚Äî

How are you going through life? Are you walking the way of grace? Grace teaches us godliness, and nothing else works. God supplies the life he calls us to through Jesus‚Äîthrough grace. He calls us to love others, to disadvantage ourselves for the sake of others. Grace can radically re-orient our whole lives, and it's our only hope for godliness. Grace leads to change. Grace gives new life.

description:
MERCH IS HERE! You can get That YouTub3 Family - The Adventurers Merch here: https://theadventuresguide.com/

Hey Adventurers,
Today we play a classic childhood game called abc freeze tag or alphabet freeze tag. Tag is an active game we use to play on the playground at recess or physical education game. With ABC tag the players can call out a word starting with the first letter of the alphabet and continuing on to the next letter of the alphabet to avoid being tagged by the person who is it. If they can call out a word in time the person who is it must go after a new player. If the person who is it can tag a person before they call out a ABC word then they are frozen until another player can tag them back in.

tags: easyjet,lego,inside cockpit,barcelona,plane,experiences,vacation,keeping kids entertained,travel,pilot,flying,flying with kids,travelling with kids,2footexplorers,explorers,i spy,play doh,london,old school,aquadoodle,kids activities,hostess,school holidays,airport,treasure hunt,things to do on a plane,learning,educational,pre-school travel,southend airport,tips,how to fly a plane
description:
How To Entertain Kids On A Plane! Keep Kids Busy On Airplane - Adventure Family Vlogs

New videos every week, so don't forget to subscribe! - https://www.bit.ly/2footexplorers
Follow us on Instagram! - https://www.instagram.com/2footexplorers/

Welcome back to another family adventure vlog! Today we will be bringing you all along on our trip to the airport! If you're wondering why we were at the airport and were going on a plane to begin with, it's because we went on a short break to visit friends in Barcelona!

Going on a plane with kids is something a lot of parents fear, as plane rides can be long and children need to be occupied almost constantly. However, there are ways to keep kids busy on an airplane, and in this video we're going to talk about how to entertain kids on a plane.

A lot of parents want to know how to entertain kids on a plane, but let's face it- keeping kids busy is hard, especially on an airplane. With this said, it is possible as you can see from today's vlog! You'll notice the different things we do to keep the kids busy and as you can tell, they work! If you're going on a trip soon on an airplane, try some of the things we did with our kids in this video with your kids!

Before you leave, hop on one of our ponies and take a ride.

Make sure you budget your time well so that you can get to it all.

We hope to see you soon at White Post Farms.

String games have been played in many cultures for thousands of years.  Some string games are believed to date back to the Stone Age!  

This summer we are trying out some traditional games.  Our aim is to get kids playing outdoors, trying new (or very old) games and activities.  It doesn't need to cost much to have fun.  Infact all you need is a piece of string and a friend.  Our young team had never seen Cats Cradle played before.  They really enjoyed getting in a muddle!

Cats cradle is normally played with two people and a piece of string.  Your sting needs to be approx 120cm long, tied into a circle.  The cradle is passed back and forwards between the players creating different patterns.  It's a game that requires concentration, good communication and team work.  We would recommend this for age 7+.  It's lots of fun, but very challenging too!

Why not give it a go?  What patterns can you make?  Keep repeating the pattern by pinching the crosses and you should end up back with the original cradle shape.  Try not get in too much of a tangle!

We provide all in one waterproofs, all in one snowsuits, waterproof jackets, waterproof trousers and waterproof dungarees for children from age 9 months to 11 years. We also sell childrens swimwear including baby and childrens wetsuits, reusable swim nappies, pool shoes and beach boots.

Football has been played in Scotland since the 1400s.  That's a very, very long time ago!  Today it remains a very popular sport, with local and national teams and thousands of supporters.  People just love football, and many children dream of following in the footsteps of their favourite players. 

The Rain-shine team have been testing some traditional children's games.  This one is for all the football fans - header catch

Header catch is a great game for practising some basic football skills.  This game requires listening, concentration and good coordination.  It also teaches turn-taking and teamwork. 

The players stand in a circle with the 'captain' at the centre.  The captain throws the ball to each player in turn.  As the ball is thrown, the captain shouts out 'header' or 'catch' and the player has to return the ball in the correct manner before it touches the ground.  If the player fails toe turn the ball, they sit down and the remaining players continue play.  The last player standing is the winner. 

Our little team had so much fun, they added their own rules!  In addition to 'header' and 'catch', we also had 'knee' and 'foot'.  I think the kids found it a little harder than they expected, and it took a lot of skill to return the ball.  This game will take a bit of practice, but it was loads of fun trying it out!   Maybe one of our players will be a famous footballer one day?

title: Real-Life Outdoor Workout with Your Kids!
tags: workout,outdoor workout,at home workout,kids,mom,momlife,Physical Exercise (Interest),Health (Industry),Life,Fitness,Training
description:
I used to get so frustrated when I would try to workout from home and my kids would interrupt me.  I remember so many times when I would just quit in the middle of my workout, throw my hands up in defeat, and think to myself, "what's the point?  I can't even finish one set without the baby wanting held".  It did get easier as the kids got a little older, but along the way I realized that if I incorporate my kids into the workouts then it becomes a game for them and instead of crying to be held the whole time, they will try to do the exercises with me. Somewhere along the way I realized that it's ok if I have to take breaks because the kids need something.  It's ok if I have to modify an exercise so I can do it while holding the baby.  It's ok if I need to slow down a little on my sprints so that my kids could beat me.  Just doing something is what mattered.  I gave myself to permission to lose the all-or-nothing mentality, and that is what made all the difference.

Here is a quick real-life glimpse into what our at-home workouts might look like.  I'll put the entire workout in the link below, try it and let me know what you think!

title: Outdoor Activities for Kids- Norcross GA Children's Garden
tags: Atlanta,eco-friendly,children,garden,discovery garden,outdoor,classroom,Norcross,Georgia,activity,family-friendly,tourism,wildlife,education,downtown,best places to live,community garden,city park,outdoor activities for kids,kids outdoor games,kids outdoor playhouse
description:
Outdoor activities for kids is inspiring a new project in Norcross, GA.  Kids outdoor games and activities to encourage them to explore nature are coming to the new garden and park.  This video shows the early stages of construction. 

http://OthelloCommunications.com - 678-861-6139 - call us to find out how we can produce your next video.

Children have a natural curiosity about the world around them. 

Experts say children learn by using and stimulating their senses.  And that leads to good brain development. 

Did you know up to age 10‚Ä¶we rely on our senses to help us interpret information and build an understanding of the world around us?

But, some scientists fear that busy schedules and limited access to the outdoors at school or home is causing an increasing number of children to lose touch with nature, which is full of things that stimulate our senses.   
There is a solution.  It‚Äôs called a discovery garden or children‚Äôs garden. 

The popularity of these outdoor activities for kids in a garden setting is growing; here‚Äôs why.

Discovery gardens are a wonderful way to let children get up close and more importantly comfortable in nature.  

Often used as outdoor classrooms, discovery gardens encourage children and adults to enjoy plants, flowers, butterflies and some pretty cool insects. 
Discovery gardens allow us to use our sense of sight, smell, sound, taste, and touch.  In these gardens, we can explore habitats, uncover plant mysteries, and have fun learning about a variety of garden wildlife. 
And in case you haven‚Äôt heard ‚Äì the city of Norcross is building its first ever Discovery Garden Park.
This pile of wood chips and leaves and this barren plot of land mark the spot where the new garden park will be located.   
In the coming weeks, this vacant land will be transformed into a beautiful discovery garden the entire community can enjoy.
The Norcross Discovery Garden Park is located directly behind the Norcross Welcome Center and Baseball Museum(?) on Lawrenceville Street.
So make plans to visit the Norcross Discovery Garden Park when it opens this year.  
It‚Äôs a place where people of all ages get the chance to learn and discover the natural world around us. It will also be home to the new Norcross Community Garden. These two projects truly make Norcross, ‚ÄúA place to imagine.‚Äù

Norcross is an Atlanta suburb that is the second oldest city in Gwinnett County.  Norcross is a small city with big heart.  Norcross has great schools, parks, and culture.

Norcross is known as one of the best places to live in metro Atlanta because of its appealing character and beautiful, historic downtown district. 

This video gives you an update on the city of Norcross' construction of a new Discovery Garden Park to open in 2016

Be sure to check out more of our videos, where Lanii Dennis takes you to the places where local tourism, businesses, and product makers are thriving. 

In fact, see this video about the importance of buying local produce, meats and dairy from Georgia farmers https://youtu.be/LBkofJjOfPo

title: Higher Higher - Traditional Outdoor Games Challenge For Kids - No 5 - Rain-shine
tags: traditional outdoor play game,outdoor play,childrens waterproofs
description:
Kids waterproofs from Rain-shine

http://www.rain-shine.co.uk

SIGN UP TO OUR ENEWSLETTER FOR YOUR FREE CHAPTER FROM OUR EBOOK ON MUDDY PLAY - VISIT WWW.RAIN-SHINE.CO.UK
Let your children have fun outside whatever the weather.  Rain-shine are the supplier of quality children's waterproof clothing throughout the UK.

We provide all in one waterproofs, all in one snowsuits, waterproof jackets, waterproof trousers and waterproof dungarees for children from age 9 months to 11 years. 

This summer our little Rain-shine team are trying out some traditional games.  Many of these simple games have been forgotten with time, and we want to see if kids can still have fun learning the games their parents and grandparents played.  

Skipping games have been around for hundreds of years.  It is thought that skipping was originally a boys game, being too strenuous for girls to play!  Higher-higher is not really skipping, but it does need a skipping rope and at least three people.  

Two people hold the rope stretched tightly.  The person in the middle has to jump the rope.  The rope becomes progressively higher with each jump until the player can no longer jump cleanly over the rope.  The person who can jump the highest wins.

Higher-higher can be enjoyed by children of any age, and can be as easy or as challenging as the players wish. This may have started out as a boys game, but our girls prove that they can jump higher too!  How high can you go?

Playground Wiki

A playground, playpark, or play area is a place with a specific design to allow children to play there. It may be indoors but is typically outdoors (where it may be called a tot lot in some regions).[1] While a playground is usually designed for children, some playgrounds are designed for other age groups. Berlin's Preu√üenpark for example is designed for senior adults age 70 or higher.[citation needed] It is possible for a playground to exclude children if they are below the required age for entrance.

Modern playgrounds often have recreational equipment such as the seesaw, merry-go-round, swingset, slide, jungle gym, chin-up bars, sandbox, spring rider, trapeze rings, playhouses, and mazes, many of which help children develop physical coordination, strength, and flexibility, as well as providing recreation and enjoyment. Common in modern playgrounds are play structures that link many different pieces of equipment.

Playgrounds often also have facilities for playing informal games of adult sports, such as a baseball diamond, a skating arena, a basketball court, or a tether ball.

Public playground equipment refers to equipment intended for use in the play areas of parks, schools, child care facilities, institutions, multiple family dwellings, restaurants, resorts, and recreational developments, and other areas of public use.

A type of playground called a playscape is designed to provide a safe environment for play in a natural setting.
